# Example crontab for personal_mem automation.
#
# Replace `/home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem` with your repo
# path and `~/.cache/personal_mem/cron.log` with whatever log location
# you prefer. Sleep between research batches now lives inside the flow
# definition (vault/.mem/flows.yaml), not in cron-spacing.
#
# Install: `crontab -e` and paste the lines below (without the leading
# `#` from these comments).

# Daily research cycle: discover gaps, drain queue, refresh hubs.
0 8 * * *  cd /home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem && uv run mem flow run daily-research >> ~/.cache/personal_mem/cron.log 2>&1

# Weekly hygiene: concept and theme dedup + hub coherence.
0 4 * * 0  cd /home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem && uv run mem flow run weekly-hygiene >> ~/.cache/personal_mem/cron.log 2>&1

# News intake (optional — requires `uv pip install personal-mem[news]`).
# Pulls RSS feeds declared in vault/.mem/news_feeds.yaml into the news
# acquisition queue every two hours. The downstream /drain step is part
# of the news-cycle flow (see example-flows.yaml::news-cycle) so the
# pull stage stays cheap and reliable; LLM cost happens on drain.
0 */2 * * * cd /home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem && uv run python scripts/pull_news_feeds.py >> ~/.cache/personal_mem/news-pull.log 2>&1

# News drain (every 6h: triage + brief). Spaced from the pulls so the
# queue accumulates a useful batch before Haiku triage runs.
30 */6 * * * cd /home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem && uv run mem flow run news-cycle >> ~/.cache/personal_mem/cron.log 2>&1

# Embeddings keep-warm: refresh embeddings for any note whose updated_at
# is newer than the most recent cached embedding. Cheap — one SQL window
# query plus N OpenAI embed calls (where N is just the new/changed
# notes since the last run). Without this, similarity and hybrid
# retrieval silently degrade to FTS-only on recent content as the
# vault grows. Requires OPENAI_API_KEY in the cron environment.
15 */4 * * * cd /home/marekpal97/python_projects/personal_mem && OPENAI_API_KEY="${OPENAI_API_KEY}" uv run mem index --embed --only-new >> ~/.cache/personal_mem/embed-warm.log 2>&1

# To run a flow ad-hoc:
#   uv run mem flow list
#   uv run mem flow show daily-research
#   uv run mem flow run daily-research --dry-run
#   uv run mem flow run daily-research
